1
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:12,720
<i>What kind of soup is this?</i>

2
00:00:13,320 --> 00:00:15,919
It's lobster bisque.

3
00:00:15,920 --> 00:00:17,240
I'm allergic to shellfish.

4
00:00:18,280 --> 00:00:19,959
- Claire!
- Hey, she fainted!

5
00:00:19,960 --> 00:00:21,039
<i>You think she was lying?</i>

6
00:00:21,040 --> 00:00:22,959
<i>Has she ever had a shellfish allergy, Mom?</i>

7
00:00:22,960 --> 00:00:26,039
Chan said someone
called the press to the hotel.

8
00:00:26,040 --> 00:00:28,159
<i>Are Chan and Claire
the only ones living here?</i>

9
00:00:28,160 --> 00:00:29,559
<i>Why do you only believe them?</i>

10
00:00:29,560 --> 00:00:33,879
Since Dad isn't giving us anything anyway,
we have to take it ourselves.

11
00:00:33,880 --> 00:00:37,439
<i>Ms. Cha probably wants to
show that even if Claire is fine,</i>

12
00:00:37,440 --> 00:00:39,399
<i>she's still unfit to run the company.</i>

13
00:00:39,400 --> 00:00:41,240
<i>He's ready to answer now.</i>

14
00:00:43,640 --> 00:00:45,759
There's Mr. Chan. Would you talk to us?

15
00:00:45,760 --> 00:00:48,039
Is it true that Ms. Claire has amnesia?

16
00:00:48,040 --> 00:00:51,479
What happened to her yesterday?
Why did she suddenly pass out?

17
00:00:51,480 --> 00:00:53,479
- What actually happened?
- What's going on?

18
00:00:53,480 --> 00:00:55,399
- Care to comment?
- Can you tell us?

19
00:00:55,400 --> 00:00:58,839
I'm really sorry.
I have an urgent meeting today,

20
00:00:58,840 --> 00:01:00,759
so I can't really talk.

21
00:01:00,760 --> 00:01:04,839
As for Ms. Claire's condition,
I'll schedule a press conference later.

22
00:01:04,840 --> 00:01:07,599
- Excuse me.
- Please answer, Mr. Chan.

23
00:01:07,600 --> 00:01:10,280
I suggest you give them
a clear answer now.

24
00:01:11,240 --> 00:01:13,119
Because leaving it vague like this

25
00:01:13,120 --> 00:01:15,560
isn't good for us or your fiancée.

26
00:01:19,160 --> 00:01:20,879
What? You're confused?

27
00:01:20,880 --> 00:01:25,920
Oh, you're wondering why I'm here
and not in the executive boardroom.

28
00:01:26,680 --> 00:01:27,599
Sorry about that.

29
00:01:27,600 --> 00:01:30,360
If I hadn't leaked that,
you wouldn't have rushed over.

30
00:01:34,320 --> 00:01:37,160
If you wanted me to meet the press,

31
00:01:37,960 --> 00:01:39,799
you could have just told me.

32
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:41,560
No need to complicate things.

33
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:46,399
You should stop arguing with me
and answer the reporters.

34
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:50,639
Right now, everyone is wondering
what really happened to Khaedarun.

35
00:01:50,640 --> 00:01:52,359
How did she survive?

36
00:01:52,360 --> 00:01:53,960
Does she really have amnesia?

37
00:01:56,800 --> 00:02:00,959
Guys, if you have any questions,
you can ask Mr. Chan now.

38
00:02:00,960 --> 00:02:02,360
He's ready to answer.

39
00:02:09,960 --> 00:02:14,160
Then, I'd like to take this opportunity
to share some good news.

40
00:02:15,120 --> 00:02:17,840
Ms. Claire's injuries from the accident

41
00:02:18,520 --> 00:02:20,120
have almost 100% healed.

42
00:02:21,760 --> 00:02:24,679
As for the details of her treatment,
I can't disclose them,

43
00:02:24,680 --> 00:02:27,680
because it's private medical information.

44
00:02:28,280 --> 00:02:30,919
Yes. Oh, but there are rumors
going around that

45
00:02:30,920 --> 00:02:33,319
the reason for her long recovery

46
00:02:33,320 --> 00:02:35,439
was because she wanted to cover up

47
00:02:35,440 --> 00:02:38,159
her violence against a company employee.

48
00:02:38,160 --> 00:02:39,079
There are also rumors

49
00:02:39,080 --> 00:02:41,839
about a physical altercation
within the family. Is that true?

50
00:02:41,840 --> 00:02:43,519
- Is it true?
- Is it true, sir?

51
00:02:43,520 --> 00:02:45,279
Uh, that is not true.

52
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:47,080
We already cleared that up.

53
00:02:47,680 --> 00:02:49,920
But the thing about Claire
we haven't disclosed

54
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:52,799
is actually about her brain.

55
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:54,600
- Her brain?
- Right, Chan?

56
00:03:00,720 --> 00:03:04,479
Ms. Claire suffered a concussion
from the helicopter crash,

57
00:03:04,480 --> 00:03:06,480
leaving her with amnesia.

58
00:03:09,800 --> 00:03:13,680
But her doctor said
it's only a temporary condition.

59
00:03:14,280 --> 00:03:17,600
It will improve and go away on its own.
Please don't worry.

60
00:03:18,760 --> 00:03:21,119
As Claire's fiancé,

61
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:24,799
I'd like to take this opportunity
to thank you for your concern.

62
00:03:24,800 --> 00:03:27,079
And I want to reassure you that

63
00:03:27,080 --> 00:03:33,160
Ms. Claire will definitely recover
and return to run TGL.

64
00:03:35,240 --> 00:03:38,039
Thank you for your concern.
Please excuse me.

65
00:03:38,040 --> 00:03:39,159
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

66
00:03:39,160 --> 00:03:40,520
Thank you, sir.

67
00:03:47,200 --> 00:03:50,039
Alright, thank you for coming.

68
00:03:50,040 --> 00:03:51,359
Thank you so much.

69
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:54,040
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

70
00:05:19,320 --> 00:05:20,319
<i>She's not my niece.</i>

71
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:22,079
- I'm leaving. She's not my niece.
- Ma'am.

72
00:05:22,080 --> 00:05:23,279
- She's not my niece.
- Ma'am.

73
00:05:23,280 --> 00:05:25,400
- <i>She's not my niece.</i>
- <i>Ma'am.</i>

74
00:05:28,920 --> 00:05:30,000
Mr. Tun?

75
00:05:30,760 --> 00:05:32,119
Mr. Tun?

76
00:05:32,120 --> 00:05:33,480
Mr. Tun!

77
00:05:38,120 --> 00:05:39,239
What is it?

78
00:05:39,240 --> 00:05:41,800
I want to know how my aunt is doing.

79
00:05:42,840 --> 00:05:44,880
From what I know, she's stable.

80
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:49,240
Or did Mr. Chan tell you something?

81
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:51,919
No.

82
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:54,839
I had a dream about her, so I felt uneasy

83
00:05:54,840 --> 00:05:57,920
and wanted to know
if she's improved at all.

84
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:03,519
Like I said,
your aunt's condition is stable.

85
00:06:03,520 --> 00:06:04,719
Please don't worry.

86
00:06:04,720 --> 00:06:08,679
Hey, do you have the number of her doctor?

87
00:06:08,680 --> 00:06:10,160
I want to talk to them.

88
00:06:11,320 --> 00:06:12,240
I don't have it.

89
00:06:14,560 --> 00:06:15,640
How about this?

90
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:18,039
I'll tell Mr. Chan about this.

91
00:06:18,040 --> 00:06:21,880
Once you're better,
he'll take you to see your aunt.

92
00:06:28,560 --> 00:06:29,680
Excuse me.

93
00:06:30,560 --> 00:06:31,800
Please don't worry.

94
00:06:36,960 --> 00:06:39,040
It's time for your medicine, Ms. Claire.

95
00:06:42,640 --> 00:06:43,640
Here you go.

96
00:06:44,320 --> 00:06:45,400
Thank you.

97
00:06:48,760 --> 00:06:51,760
You're even more beautiful
in person than on TV.

98
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:54,559
You know me?

99
00:06:54,560 --> 00:06:57,039
More like who doesn't?

100
00:06:57,040 --> 00:07:01,079
I really admire you
for all the good you've done.

101
00:07:01,080 --> 00:07:04,480
This is how it should be.
The haves should help the have-nots.

102
00:07:07,360 --> 00:07:09,880
I'll be back in about two hours.

103
00:07:12,680 --> 00:07:13,600
Excuse me.

104
00:07:14,720 --> 00:07:15,919
Yes?

105
00:07:15,920 --> 00:07:16,999
Well.

106
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:19,040
Could I borrow your phone?

107
00:07:21,320 --> 00:07:22,639
<i>I want to reassure you that</i>

108
00:07:22,640 --> 00:07:25,559
<i>Ms. Claire will definitely recover</i>

109
00:07:25,560 --> 00:07:29,080
<i>and return to run TGL.</i>

110
00:07:29,680 --> 00:07:31,280
<i>Thank you for your concern.</i>

111
00:07:39,880 --> 00:07:43,879
I don't understand
why you would do something like that.

112
00:07:43,880 --> 00:07:45,479
You know that no matter

113
00:07:45,480 --> 00:07:48,120
how badly you've
ruined Claire's reputation,

114
00:07:48,800 --> 00:07:51,680
the chairman will
never replace her with you.

115
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:53,840
Yes, I know.

116
00:07:55,400 --> 00:07:56,360
So what?

117
00:07:58,480 --> 00:08:01,120
Then why did
you call an executive meeting?

118
00:08:03,080 --> 00:08:06,320
I just wanted you and Claire
to prove yourselves.

119
00:08:06,840 --> 00:08:09,759
Didn't you tell the press
she's ready to work?

120
00:08:09,760 --> 00:08:14,079
Now's the time for you and Claire
to prove to the management team

121
00:08:14,080 --> 00:08:15,960
she's really ready to work.

122
00:08:16,920 --> 00:08:20,199
Oh dear, it's almost time for the meeting.

123
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:22,920
I suggest you hurry and prepare.

124
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:38,839
Tun.

125
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:41,120
Bring her to the company right now.

126
00:08:41,840 --> 00:08:43,880
Chan, she's gone.

127
00:08:46,480 --> 00:08:48,440
What do you mean she's gone?

128
00:08:49,120 --> 00:08:52,800
I think she found out that
her aunt's condition worsened.

129
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:56,119
And I asked
the nurse who was with her last.

130
00:08:56,120 --> 00:09:00,119
<i>She said Ms. Claire borrowed her phone
to call somebody.</i>

131
00:09:00,120 --> 00:09:02,159
<i>And I've checked.</i>

132
00:09:02,160 --> 00:09:04,280
It's her aunt's hospital number.

133
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:18,200
Yes, Ms. Nalin who's in the private room.

134
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:21,400
Yes, Mr. Nitchan is her sponsor.

135
00:09:24,760 --> 00:09:26,079
What do you mean?

136
00:09:26,080 --> 00:09:28,240
You said she's still in the ICU.

137
00:09:29,760 --> 00:09:32,560
Ms. Nalin is in
a private room, not the ICU.

138
00:09:49,520 --> 00:09:51,639
Hey, are you okay, ma'am?

139
00:09:51,640 --> 00:09:54,079
Would you like a wheelchair?

140
00:09:54,080 --> 00:09:54,999
I'm fine.

141
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:56,559
- Can you manage?
- Yes. Thank you.

142
00:09:56,560 --> 00:09:57,840
Walk slowly.

143
00:10:01,080 --> 00:10:02,479
Excuse me.

144
00:10:02,480 --> 00:10:05,559
I'm here for an ICU patient.
Her name is Nalin.

145
00:10:05,560 --> 00:10:08,239
- Which way is it?
- Uh, what's her last name?

146
00:10:08,240 --> 00:10:10,360
- Phiandaidee.
- A moment, please.

147
00:10:11,960 --> 00:10:14,239
She's in ICU 3. It's that way.

148
00:10:14,240 --> 00:10:15,640
Thank you.

149
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:20,080
Ms. Claire.

150
00:10:22,400 --> 00:10:24,280
It really is you.

151
00:10:26,120 --> 00:10:29,039
Excuse me, do we know each other?

152
00:10:29,040 --> 00:10:31,480
I don't recognize anyone these days.

153
00:10:33,080 --> 00:10:34,720
You don't know me.

154
00:10:35,320 --> 00:10:36,760
But I know you.

155
00:10:37,680 --> 00:10:39,760
Because you hurt my daughter.

156
00:10:40,880 --> 00:10:43,560
You must be mistaken.
I've never hurt anyone.

157
00:10:45,360 --> 00:10:46,559
Mistaken?

158
00:10:46,560 --> 00:10:49,799
What if I tell you that
I am the mother of Mina,

159
00:10:49,800 --> 00:10:52,479
the employee you assaulted?

160
00:10:52,480 --> 00:10:53,760
Will you remember then?

161
00:11:00,800 --> 00:11:03,159
<i>Unacceptable.
How many times do I have to tell you?</i>

162
00:11:03,160 --> 00:11:05,359
<i>You're so stupid. Stupid, stupid, stupid!</i>

163
00:11:05,360 --> 00:11:06,519
<i>How can you be this stupid?</i>

164
00:11:06,520 --> 00:11:08,640
<i>- How many times do I have to tell you?
- I'm sorry.</i>

165
00:11:10,120 --> 00:11:13,959
My daughter worked her ass off for you,

166
00:11:13,960 --> 00:11:15,679
but you,

167
00:11:15,680 --> 00:11:18,239
you accused her of stealing.

168
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:21,119
Her record was ruined
and she couldn't apply for a job anywhere.

169
00:11:21,120 --> 00:11:22,080
Ma'am, listen...

170
00:11:23,840 --> 00:11:26,560
My daughter Mina was so stressed

171
00:11:27,920 --> 00:11:29,960
that she took pills to end her life.

172
00:11:31,280 --> 00:11:33,320
Luckily, I found her in time.

173
00:11:34,920 --> 00:11:37,199
But she lost her mind.

174
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:39,399
Because of you! All because of you!

175
00:11:39,400 --> 00:11:41,639
- Why did you do that to her?! Why?!
- Ma'am.

176
00:11:41,640 --> 00:11:42,640
- Ma'am.
- No!

177
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:47,840
What if you got splashed with acid?

178
00:11:48,440 --> 00:11:50,120
No! Mind your own business!

179
00:11:51,760 --> 00:11:54,080
You, you must burn in hell.

180
00:12:00,880 --> 00:12:02,359
No, ma'am!

181
00:12:02,360 --> 00:12:04,239
This time it's just water!

182
00:12:04,240 --> 00:12:06,439
Next time you'll get the real thing!

183
00:12:06,440 --> 00:12:07,439
You must pay

184
00:12:07,440 --> 00:12:08,439
for what you did to my daughter!

185
00:12:08,440 --> 00:12:10,479
Get off me! You must pay for what you did!

186
00:12:10,480 --> 00:12:13,720
You bitch! Get off me! Get off me!

187
00:12:25,560 --> 00:12:26,960
Are you still in shock?

188
00:12:29,400 --> 00:12:31,240
Are you going to
press charges against her?

189
00:12:31,840 --> 00:12:32,880
I think so.

190
00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:36,880
Why? Do you want to
press additional charges?

191
00:12:37,520 --> 00:12:39,520
No, I mean...

192
00:12:40,360 --> 00:12:41,480
I...

193
00:12:42,520 --> 00:12:45,200
I don't want you to press charges.

194
00:12:47,480 --> 00:12:50,719
I think she's stressed enough as it is.

195
00:12:50,720 --> 00:12:52,119
Her daughter is unwell.

196
00:12:52,120 --> 00:12:55,600
And I don't want her to face
a lawsuit on top of that.

197
00:12:56,240 --> 00:12:58,719
If we do that and just let it go,

198
00:12:58,720 --> 00:13:03,160
and one day she throws acid
on you for real, what then?

199
00:13:09,520 --> 00:13:10,960
What if we try another way?

200
00:13:11,560 --> 00:13:16,039
Today, she did it because she's angry
that her daughter was mistreated, right?

201
00:13:16,040 --> 00:13:20,760
But what if we step in
and take responsibility for what...

202
00:13:22,720 --> 00:13:26,520
what Ms. Claire did to her daughter?

203
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:28,600
Would that help?

204
00:13:34,360 --> 00:13:35,600
I'll think about it.

205
00:13:37,240 --> 00:13:38,160
Thank you.

206
00:13:43,240 --> 00:13:45,920
For considering that, and...

207
00:13:46,800 --> 00:13:48,680
for saving me.

208
00:13:50,120 --> 00:13:51,200
Thank you?

209
00:13:52,560 --> 00:13:54,800
Shouldn't you say sorry instead?

210
00:13:55,640 --> 00:13:57,320
If you'd listened to me today

211
00:13:57,960 --> 00:14:01,240
instead of running off,
this wouldn't have happened.

212
00:14:03,120 --> 00:14:07,239
I forgot you went through all the trouble
to make me look like Ms. Claire.

213
00:14:07,240 --> 00:14:09,239
If anything happened to my face,

214
00:14:09,240 --> 00:14:11,639
you'd be worried I wouldn't
look like her anymore.

215
00:14:11,640 --> 00:14:13,919
If you have nothing
nice to say, follow me.

216
00:14:13,920 --> 00:14:15,440
You can go by yourself.

217
00:14:17,120 --> 00:14:19,199
Why? Where are you running off to now?

218
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:21,799
You know why I'm here.

219
00:14:21,800 --> 00:14:23,400
I came to see my aunt.

220
00:14:29,800 --> 00:14:34,680
Do you guys know
why I called this urgent meeting?

221
00:14:36,480 --> 00:14:38,040
Do you know, Chris?

222
00:14:41,200 --> 00:14:42,680
Is it about Ms. Claire?

223
00:14:45,240 --> 00:14:46,120
It is.

224
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:51,719
I take you guys saw the interview
Nitchan, Ms. Claire's fiancé, gave.

225
00:14:51,720 --> 00:14:56,200
He said Ms. Claire has amnesia
because of a concussion.

226
00:14:56,840 --> 00:14:59,919
That's why I called an urgent meeting.

227
00:14:59,920 --> 00:15:02,279
I want all of you to sign your names

228
00:15:02,280 --> 00:15:05,519
to remove Ms. Claire
from her position as CEO of TGL.

229
00:15:05,520 --> 00:15:09,559
And you hid the fact that
my aunt's condition had worsened.

230
00:15:09,560 --> 00:15:12,560
If I hadn't called the hospital,
I wouldn't have known.

231
00:15:14,320 --> 00:15:15,720
You have to come with me.

232
00:15:16,320 --> 00:15:19,279
I'm not going anywhere
until I see my aunt.

233
00:15:19,280 --> 00:15:23,879
This must be a shock and you're worried
signing it would be a violation.

234
00:15:23,880 --> 00:15:25,439
But don't worry.

235
00:15:25,440 --> 00:15:28,479
Our signing here will let
the chairman know that

236
00:15:28,480 --> 00:15:30,720
we all truly love TGL.

237
00:15:31,560 --> 00:15:32,799
But on the other hand,

238
00:15:32,800 --> 00:15:37,519
if you don't sign, as Acting CEO,

239
00:15:37,520 --> 00:15:41,239
I will have to use
my power to dismiss you.

240
00:15:41,240 --> 00:15:44,520
Because not signing
would be betraying TGL.

241
00:15:52,480 --> 00:15:53,560
Go ahead.

242
00:15:54,360 --> 00:15:55,640
Please sign.

243
00:16:11,320 --> 00:16:13,840
No one will be dismissed today.

244
00:16:17,960 --> 00:16:21,720
Because the only person
who has the power to do that is...

245
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:23,840
Ms. Khaedarun.

246
00:16:38,840 --> 00:16:40,000
Hello, Ms. Vice Chairman.

247
00:16:55,920 --> 00:16:56,840
Hello, Claire.

248
00:16:58,240 --> 00:16:59,440
Are you fully recovered?

249
00:17:01,240 --> 00:17:03,720
Before you discuss anything
with Ms. Claire,

250
00:17:04,640 --> 00:17:09,800
you should know that
that seat belongs to her.

251
00:17:20,040 --> 00:17:23,040
Go ahead. Why don't you greet everyone?

252
00:17:37,840 --> 00:17:39,120
Hello, everyone.

253
00:17:48,120 --> 00:17:49,320
Everyone,

254
00:17:49,880 --> 00:17:52,839
you all see now that Claire having amnesia

255
00:17:52,840 --> 00:17:55,559
has caused
our stock to drop significantly.

256
00:17:55,560 --> 00:17:57,479
So, please don't worry.

257
00:17:57,480 --> 00:17:59,919
What we are all doing right now

258
00:17:59,920 --> 00:18:02,600
is definitely for the good of the company.

259
00:18:03,200 --> 00:18:04,040
Please sign.

260
00:18:04,560 --> 00:18:07,000
Please stop using
the company as an excuse.

261
00:18:07,800 --> 00:18:11,720
You all know scheduling a meeting
behind someone's back is wrong.

262
00:18:13,440 --> 00:18:17,760
Isn't letting someone incompetent
run the company even more wrong?

263
00:18:18,680 --> 00:18:20,199
According to the bylaws,

264
00:18:20,200 --> 00:18:23,440
if an executive is unable
to perform their duties,

265
00:18:24,040 --> 00:18:27,360
we all have the right
to find their replacement.

266
00:18:28,240 --> 00:18:29,440
Isn't that how it is?

267
00:18:33,160 --> 00:18:33,999
Alright, everyone.

268
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:35,719
Don't worry.

269
00:18:35,720 --> 00:18:36,880
Please sign.

270
00:18:38,560 --> 00:18:39,800
Don't just stand there!

271
00:18:40,400 --> 00:18:41,840
Sign it!

272
00:18:45,440 --> 00:18:47,719
I'm warning you to stop this meeting.

273
00:18:47,720 --> 00:18:49,359
- Otherwise...
- What?

274
00:18:49,360 --> 00:18:51,959
Are you going to call the chairman? Huh?

275
00:18:51,960 --> 00:18:53,479
Go ahead.

276
00:18:53,480 --> 00:18:57,480
If you're not afraid these things
will affect his health, then go ahead.

277
00:18:58,920 --> 00:19:00,240
Go ahead.

278
00:19:00,840 --> 00:19:02,280
Do it.

279
00:19:03,960 --> 00:19:05,040
How annoying.

280
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:11,000
I said stay still.
Is it so hard? I don't get it.

281
00:19:18,720 --> 00:19:20,640
- Call him!
- Enough!

282
00:19:27,600 --> 00:19:29,280
Even though I have amnesia,

283
00:19:30,280 --> 00:19:32,720
I'm ready to continue running TGL.

284
00:19:33,440 --> 00:19:36,360
If you have
a problem with that, then quit.

285
00:20:21,640 --> 00:20:23,280
This is Ms. Claire's office.

286
00:20:32,600 --> 00:20:33,840
What's wrong?

287
00:20:36,120 --> 00:20:37,320
I'm scared.

288
00:20:37,960 --> 00:20:40,880
I never attended a meeting that formal.

289
00:20:42,040 --> 00:20:44,600
People never looked at me like that.

290
00:20:47,240 --> 00:20:49,640
But for your first time,
you did very well.

291
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:53,120
The way you commanded them.

292
00:20:55,120 --> 00:20:58,800
I just thought about
what Ms. Claire would do at that moment.

293
00:21:00,160 --> 00:21:01,200
I understand.

294
00:21:01,720 --> 00:21:03,720
But you'll get used to it after a while.

295
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:06,879
You rest in this room for now.

296
00:21:06,880 --> 00:21:08,960
I'll have someone bring you water.

297
00:21:13,160 --> 00:21:15,239
I came here as you told me to.

298
00:21:15,240 --> 00:21:18,760
You must promise me
that you will save my aunt.

299
00:21:23,040 --> 00:21:24,560
Don't worry about that.

300
00:21:26,520 --> 00:21:29,279
I'll find the best doctors
to treat your aunt.

301
00:21:29,280 --> 00:21:32,199
For now, rest and get over the shock.

302
00:21:32,200 --> 00:21:33,600
And don't go anywhere.

303
00:21:54,200 --> 00:21:56,160
Why is my aunt like this?

304
00:21:59,760 --> 00:22:02,199
Didn't you say
you'd take the best care of her?

305
00:22:02,200 --> 00:22:04,879
Then why did her condition get worse?

306
00:22:04,880 --> 00:22:06,599
Huh? Why is she like this?

307
00:22:06,600 --> 00:22:07,759
Do what you promised!

308
00:22:07,760 --> 00:22:09,520
- Do what you said!
- Hey!

309
00:22:10,760 --> 00:22:13,200
Your aunt's condition is unpredictable.

310
00:22:14,360 --> 00:22:16,520
You know I'm doing everything I can.

311
00:22:38,080 --> 00:22:39,560
Aunt...

312
00:22:43,120 --> 00:22:44,800
Auntie.

313
00:22:49,080 --> 00:22:50,120
Aunt.

314
00:22:52,160 --> 00:22:54,000
Hey, don't cry.

315
00:22:54,800 --> 00:22:55,680
- Aunt.
- Hey.

316
00:22:56,480 --> 00:22:57,480
Hey.

317
00:22:58,040 --> 00:22:59,280
I said don't cry.

318
00:23:00,960 --> 00:23:03,480
I didn't bring you here
to say goodbye to her.

319
00:23:06,560 --> 00:23:09,640
I brought you here
to tell your aunt to fight.

320
00:23:11,560 --> 00:23:13,920
You're the only person
who can bring her back.

321
00:23:16,080 --> 00:23:17,840
Do you understand what I'm saying?

322
00:23:38,960 --> 00:23:40,120
Aunt.

323
00:23:41,520 --> 00:23:43,440
You must come back to me.

324
00:23:45,600 --> 00:23:47,400
I know that you're a fighter.

325
00:23:49,520 --> 00:23:51,080
You must not give up.

326
00:23:54,680 --> 00:23:56,760
And I won't give up either.

327
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:02,760
You must come back to me.

328
00:24:05,480 --> 00:24:06,560
Okay?

329
00:24:16,720 --> 00:24:18,200
<i>Ms. Claire.</i>

330
00:24:26,400 --> 00:24:27,400
Yes?

331
00:24:27,960 --> 00:24:29,719
<i>Your friends are here to see you.</i>

332
00:24:29,720 --> 00:24:31,800
<i>They're waiting in the lounge.</i>

333
00:24:33,400 --> 00:24:34,520
Friends?

334
00:24:36,200 --> 00:24:37,879
- So beautiful.
- Really.

335
00:24:37,880 --> 00:24:38,800
I love it.

336
00:24:40,040 --> 00:24:41,320
Ms. Yo, Ms. Patch.

337
00:24:42,280 --> 00:24:43,120
Claire!

338
00:24:43,760 --> 00:24:45,039
You're really not dead.

339
00:24:45,040 --> 00:24:47,880
As soon as we heard, we rushed over here.

340
00:24:48,480 --> 00:24:50,839
Do you know how shocked
we were when we heard

341
00:24:50,840 --> 00:24:53,040
the helicopter you were in crashed?

342
00:24:53,600 --> 00:24:54,960
Who's that?

343
00:24:55,800 --> 00:24:57,919
She's interviewing me. Her name is Jinla.

344
00:24:57,920 --> 00:24:59,839
- Hi, Jin.
- Hi, Jin.

345
00:24:59,840 --> 00:25:01,960
What's wrong?
Why are you making that face?

346
00:25:02,680 --> 00:25:06,520
Uh, I'm a fan of Ms. Patchy.

347
00:25:08,280 --> 00:25:09,840
Uh, I'm fine.

348
00:25:10,880 --> 00:25:14,560
So about the amnesia, is it true?

349
00:25:16,040 --> 00:25:17,800
Yes.

350
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:22,640
So you don't remember
you have to pay our appearance fees?

351
00:25:23,960 --> 00:25:25,160
Appearance fees?

352
00:25:27,640 --> 00:25:28,720
What appearance fees?

353
00:25:29,440 --> 00:25:33,000
The appearance fees
for us to be your friends.

354
00:25:34,360 --> 00:25:35,720
Hired to be my friends?

355
00:25:37,000 --> 00:25:38,160
What does that mean?

356
00:25:39,560 --> 00:25:41,279
Come on, Ms. Claire.

357
00:25:41,280 --> 00:25:43,719
Did you really think we were friends?

358
00:25:43,720 --> 00:25:46,239
You hired the two of us to be your friends

359
00:25:46,240 --> 00:25:49,559
so you'd look more popular
and glamorous than other socialites.

360
00:25:49,560 --> 00:25:51,359
- Hi.
- Hey.

361
00:25:51,360 --> 00:25:53,959
- Hey.
- Hey.

362
00:25:53,960 --> 00:25:55,360
- My turn.
- Come on.

363
00:26:02,040 --> 00:26:04,200
And you two used Claire's reputation

364
00:26:04,920 --> 00:26:06,480
to bump up your own rates.

365
00:26:09,040 --> 00:26:14,520
You also use Ms. Claire's connections
in your own businesses, am I right?

366
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:19,879
Okay, we don't argue with that.

367
00:26:19,880 --> 00:26:21,839
But...

368
00:26:21,840 --> 00:26:25,520
we came today is to ask about
the fees we previously agreed on.

369
00:26:26,120 --> 00:26:29,279
Our fees, including compensation
for our time, are...

370
00:26:29,280 --> 00:26:30,559
three million each.

371
00:26:30,560 --> 00:26:34,320
- Six million in total.
- Six million?

372
00:26:36,000 --> 00:26:37,440
Didn't we agree...

373
00:26:38,280 --> 00:26:39,720
at two million each?

374
00:26:40,320 --> 00:26:41,159
Yes.

375
00:26:41,160 --> 00:26:43,679
It would be if it was paid back then.

376
00:26:43,680 --> 00:26:46,319
But there's a six-month delay fee.

377
00:26:46,320 --> 00:26:48,439
We didn't just make up this number.

378
00:26:48,440 --> 00:26:51,040
It's based on
the contract she made with us.

379
00:26:52,200 --> 00:26:55,119
We actually came here to as a courtesy.

380
00:26:55,120 --> 00:26:57,760
Don't force us to handle this legally.

381
00:26:58,600 --> 00:26:59,639
Legally?

382
00:26:59,640 --> 00:27:03,359
If you want to take legal action,

383
00:27:03,360 --> 00:27:05,040
I wouldn't mind at all.

384
00:27:05,920 --> 00:27:09,120
But you must have not read
the contract carefully enough.

385
00:27:10,040 --> 00:27:14,039
According to the contract,
besides specifying the payment amount,

386
00:27:14,040 --> 00:27:16,679
it also states
the agreement will become void

387
00:27:16,680 --> 00:27:19,079
if you disclose
its details to anyone else.

388
00:27:19,080 --> 00:27:20,720
And if you sue,

389
00:27:22,120 --> 00:27:24,800
you will be the ones
breaching the contract.

390
00:27:26,160 --> 00:27:28,439
Are you trying to cheat us, Ms. Claire?

391
00:27:28,440 --> 00:27:29,960
Rich and a cheat.

392
00:27:30,720 --> 00:27:33,039
I didn't say that I wouldn't pay.

393
00:27:33,040 --> 00:27:36,559
I said all that just to remind you

394
00:27:36,560 --> 00:27:38,760
Ms. Claire doesn't like being threatened.

395
00:27:40,280 --> 00:27:41,360
As for your fees,

396
00:27:42,560 --> 00:27:44,120
I'll take care of it.

397
00:27:44,720 --> 00:27:46,760
Is there anything else?

398
00:27:50,080 --> 00:27:52,360
No. Let's go.

399
00:28:11,680 --> 00:28:12,920
Why did you come?

400
00:28:13,840 --> 00:28:15,200
Hey, you're hurting me.

401
00:28:16,880 --> 00:28:19,159
Don't you know how dangerous this is?

402
00:28:19,160 --> 00:28:21,720
What if it wasn't those two
who came to see you?

403
00:28:22,720 --> 00:28:26,040
You make it sound like there are
others who want to hurt Ms. Claire.

404
00:28:28,160 --> 00:28:30,079
You're not answering my question.

405
00:28:30,080 --> 00:28:31,359
Well...

406
00:28:31,360 --> 00:28:35,999
I'm trying to explain it to you,
but you just keep yelling at me.

407
00:28:36,000 --> 00:28:38,560
Would you hear me out for once?

408
00:28:41,240 --> 00:28:45,719
I came because I was told that
my friends were here to see me.

409
00:28:45,720 --> 00:28:46,640
That's why.

410
00:28:47,240 --> 00:28:49,879
Friends? Tell me the truth.

411
00:28:49,880 --> 00:28:53,840
By "friends," did you think
they were your friends or Claire's?

412
00:28:57,120 --> 00:28:58,600
You don't have to answer me.

413
00:29:00,240 --> 00:29:02,280
Because deep down you know the answer.

414
00:29:06,680 --> 00:29:07,520
Yes.

415
00:29:08,240 --> 00:29:11,919
I admit that for a split second,
I thought they might be my friends

416
00:29:11,920 --> 00:29:12,960
who know me

417
00:29:14,360 --> 00:29:16,280
and know who I really am.

418
00:29:19,880 --> 00:29:20,919
Hello, Ms. Cha.

419
00:29:20,920 --> 00:29:23,039
Would you sign this for me?

420
00:29:23,040 --> 00:29:26,079
Oi! Put it in my office!

421
00:29:26,080 --> 00:29:27,000
Go away!

422
00:29:28,160 --> 00:29:29,240
I'm sorry.

423
00:29:52,920 --> 00:29:54,079
Hey.

424
00:29:54,080 --> 00:29:56,280
Do you think
Ms. Cha heard our conversation?

425
00:29:58,880 --> 00:30:01,000
Never mind that. I'll handle it.

426
00:30:17,120 --> 00:30:20,280
Hello, Ms. Rose. It's been a while.

427
00:30:22,840 --> 00:30:27,639
Well, I have something about
Ms. Claire to share with you.

428
00:30:27,640 --> 00:30:30,360
I'm not sure if you still want to know.

429
00:31:02,920 --> 00:31:05,000
Um, thanks.

430
00:31:07,880 --> 00:31:09,519
I'm sorry.

431
00:31:09,520 --> 00:31:11,600
Did I wake you?

432
00:31:12,560 --> 00:31:13,599
No, no.

433
00:31:13,600 --> 00:31:16,639
Well, I thought your tea
had probably gone cold,

434
00:31:16,640 --> 00:31:18,199
so I brought you a new pot.

435
00:31:18,200 --> 00:31:20,080
Oh, it's alright.

436
00:31:20,880 --> 00:31:24,160
I wasn't asleep,
just resting my eyes a bit.

437
00:31:29,560 --> 00:31:30,640
Smells so good.

438
00:31:32,160 --> 00:31:33,320
What did you put in it?

439
00:31:35,920 --> 00:31:38,000
Just a little bit of honey.

440
00:31:40,880 --> 00:31:43,760
I thought it was poison or cyanide.

441
00:31:55,480 --> 00:31:56,640
Are you happy now?

442
00:31:58,560 --> 00:32:00,679
If I really wanted you dead,

443
00:32:00,680 --> 00:32:03,200
I'd have much
better ways than poisoning you.

444
00:32:03,880 --> 00:32:07,679
Do you have any idea
how much it breaks my heart

445
00:32:07,680 --> 00:32:10,320
that you believe Claire
that I cheated on you?

446
00:32:11,200 --> 00:32:13,519
You believe her
because she said she had proof.

447
00:32:13,520 --> 00:32:15,600
But where is that proof?

448
00:32:22,040 --> 00:32:25,600
You can leave.
I want to stay here a while longer.

449
00:32:27,200 --> 00:32:30,399
I know that you're being cold towards me

450
00:32:30,400 --> 00:32:33,079
because you want Claire's memory to return

451
00:32:33,080 --> 00:32:34,800
so you get the proof she claimed to have.

452
00:32:39,040 --> 00:32:40,839
But didn't it occur to you

453
00:32:40,840 --> 00:32:43,639
that if Claire had proof I cheated on you,

454
00:32:43,640 --> 00:32:45,680
she would've used it by now?

455
00:32:46,880 --> 00:32:48,919
You know how your granddaughter is like.

456
00:32:48,920 --> 00:32:50,999
She would've already shown it to you

457
00:32:51,000 --> 00:32:53,360
and kicked me out of this house.

458
00:33:04,160 --> 00:33:05,560
Thanks for the tea.

459
00:33:06,200 --> 00:33:07,680
And don't bring it again.

460
00:34:07,120 --> 00:34:08,040
Hello, Doctor.

461
00:34:09,440 --> 00:34:12,159
Have you heard about
Claire's shellfish allergy?

462
00:34:41,040 --> 00:34:42,520
Where did she keep it?

463
00:34:45,199 --> 00:34:48,280
Mr. Chan, Ms. Claire, the chairman
wants to see you in the study.

464
00:34:51,760 --> 00:34:53,320
Will it be alright?

465
00:34:56,480 --> 00:34:57,800
He was worried sick about you.

466
00:34:58,480 --> 00:35:01,639
If you're back and don't go see him,
it will raise suspicions.

467
00:35:01,640 --> 00:35:03,280
Oh, but...

468
00:35:12,240 --> 00:35:13,080
Claire!

469
00:35:13,760 --> 00:35:14,800
Grandpa.

470
00:35:18,800 --> 00:35:20,320
How are you? Feeling better?

471
00:35:21,240 --> 00:35:22,120
Yes.

472
00:35:23,160 --> 00:35:24,120
I'm sorry.

473
00:35:25,360 --> 00:35:30,120
Chan said you were shocked
when I had the allergic reaction.

474
00:35:31,000 --> 00:35:32,800
How is your heart doing?

475
00:35:35,600 --> 00:35:36,840
Who are you really?

476
00:35:49,280 --> 00:35:50,640
I'm asking...

477
00:35:51,280 --> 00:35:53,760
because I can't believe
you actually care about me.

478
00:35:57,640 --> 00:36:00,839
I had no idea that
amnesia would make you this lovely.

479
00:36:00,840 --> 00:36:05,200
If I'd known, I would've had Chan
give you amnesia a long time ago.

480
00:36:10,800 --> 00:36:12,080
Just kidding.

481
00:36:12,760 --> 00:36:16,000
I love you either way
because you're my only grandchild.

482
00:36:17,560 --> 00:36:20,439
By the way, where were you guys?

483
00:36:20,440 --> 00:36:22,880
I called the hospital.
They said you left hours ago.

484
00:36:25,400 --> 00:36:27,439
I had to go sign some documents
at the company,

485
00:36:27,440 --> 00:36:29,759
so I took the opportunity
to bring Claire along

486
00:36:29,760 --> 00:36:32,199
in hopes that it might trigger her memory.

487
00:36:32,200 --> 00:36:34,679
I'm sorry for bringing her back late.

488
00:36:34,680 --> 00:36:35,760
It's alright.

489
00:36:38,720 --> 00:36:40,360
I was just curious

490
00:36:41,520 --> 00:36:43,119
why you're allergic to shellfish.

491
00:36:43,120 --> 00:36:44,600
Because you weren't before.

492
00:36:45,920 --> 00:36:48,360
So I called the doctor at your hospital.

493
00:36:49,640 --> 00:36:52,680
And what did the doctor say, sir?

494
00:36:55,600 --> 00:36:56,520
Well...

495
00:37:01,320 --> 00:37:02,920
They couldn't really say.

496
00:37:03,640 --> 00:37:06,519
Unless Claire goes in
for a detailed check-up.

497
00:37:06,520 --> 00:37:09,479
Because some people
aren't allergic as kids

498
00:37:09,480 --> 00:37:10,560
but develop it as adults.

499
00:37:12,640 --> 00:37:13,840
But don't worry.

500
00:37:15,000 --> 00:37:18,640
I told Aunt Rin there won't be
any shellfish served in this house.

501
00:37:20,080 --> 00:37:22,160
I will be more careful too.

502
00:37:24,160 --> 00:37:27,680
I just wanted to make sure
this kind of thing won't happen again.

503
00:37:29,320 --> 00:37:31,759
How many months did we lose?

504
00:37:31,760 --> 00:37:35,120
And I don't want
to see you like that again.

505
00:37:35,800 --> 00:37:36,840
Okay?

506
00:37:42,400 --> 00:37:43,799
Don't worry, sir.

507
00:37:43,800 --> 00:37:47,000
I won't let something like that
happen ever again.

508
00:37:49,240 --> 00:37:51,279
Then, go get some rest.

509
00:37:51,280 --> 00:37:52,919
- I will.
- Go, Chan.

510
00:37:52,920 --> 00:37:53,880
Sir.

511
00:37:54,600 --> 00:37:55,680
I'll walk you there.

512
00:38:25,000 --> 00:38:26,160
What's with you?

513
00:38:27,440 --> 00:38:31,280
Hey, weren't you shocked at all
when he asked me who I was?

514
00:38:59,560 --> 00:39:02,159
Didn't I tell you to watch what you say?

515
00:39:02,160 --> 00:39:03,440
You could've been more gentle.

516
00:39:04,200 --> 00:39:06,080
There wasn't anybody around.

517
00:39:15,120 --> 00:39:16,599
I was scared.

518
00:39:16,600 --> 00:39:18,560
- I thought...
- Stop it.

519
00:39:19,120 --> 00:39:21,160
We're not talking about this anymore.

520
00:39:27,000 --> 00:39:28,000
Hey.

521
00:39:29,200 --> 00:39:30,200
Are you sure...

522
00:39:31,520 --> 00:39:34,400
he won't suspect anything
about my shellfish allergy?

523
00:39:37,400 --> 00:39:40,559
Yes. He got his answer.

524
00:39:40,560 --> 00:39:42,400
And he got it from a doctor.

525
00:39:59,520 --> 00:40:01,440
You just leave the tablet out like this?

526
00:40:05,080 --> 00:40:08,400
Hey, why didn't
you keep it somewhere safe?

527
00:40:09,880 --> 00:40:12,519
What if someone saw it,
or the maid came in to clean,

528
00:40:12,520 --> 00:40:14,320
and look at the info inside?

529
00:40:15,720 --> 00:40:18,719
I thought... I thought I kept it safe.

530
00:40:18,720 --> 00:40:20,360
I don't know how it ended up out here.

531
00:40:21,480 --> 00:40:24,560
Uh, okay,
I'm gonna find a new place for it.

532
00:40:52,840 --> 00:40:54,200
Hey!

533
00:40:54,800 --> 00:40:56,240
Is something wrong?

534
00:41:02,720 --> 00:41:04,320
Oh, nothing.

535
00:41:08,560 --> 00:41:12,040
The floor was slippery, so I got startled.

536
00:41:17,960 --> 00:41:20,399
It's really nothing. I just got startled.

537
00:41:20,400 --> 00:41:21,800
You can leave.

538
00:41:22,520 --> 00:41:25,720
Uh, I think I'm going to
take a shower and change.

539
00:41:26,480 --> 00:41:29,000
Go on. It's really nothing. Go.

540
00:41:34,840 --> 00:41:36,640
If you need anything, call me.

541
00:41:57,000 --> 00:41:58,520
You can come out now, Aunt Rin.

542
00:41:59,360 --> 00:42:01,080
Chan is gone.

543
00:42:21,960 --> 00:42:23,240
Why didn't you tell him?

544
00:42:24,520 --> 00:42:28,159
I didn't see how telling him
would make anything better.

545
00:42:28,160 --> 00:42:30,960
It might even make things worse
and make Grandpa worried.

546
00:42:32,600 --> 00:42:34,280
Why did you come in here?

547
00:42:38,840 --> 00:42:42,999
You probably don't remember
what you did to me.

548
00:42:43,000 --> 00:42:47,479
You told your grandfather
you had proof I was having an affair.

549
00:42:47,480 --> 00:42:49,720
That's why he's been cold towards me.

550
00:42:53,520 --> 00:42:54,359
So...

551
00:42:54,360 --> 00:42:58,520
So I wanted to see
if you really have proof like you claimed.

552
00:43:01,200 --> 00:43:02,920
To my knowledge,

553
00:43:03,800 --> 00:43:05,440
there is none.

554
00:43:08,800 --> 00:43:11,040
And what's inside that tablet?

555
00:43:12,720 --> 00:43:16,480
If you're being sincere,
you have to let me see.

556
00:43:18,360 --> 00:43:20,080
- What's in there?
- Hold on.

557
00:43:25,280 --> 00:43:26,360
Show me.

558
00:43:34,280 --> 00:43:35,760
I said show me.

559
00:43:39,040 --> 00:43:40,520
It does exist, doesn't it?

560
00:43:42,440 --> 00:43:44,639
What does? What do you mean?

561
00:43:44,640 --> 00:43:46,520
The proof that you cheated on him.

562
00:43:47,760 --> 00:43:50,559
You claimed I made the whole thing up,

563
00:43:50,560 --> 00:43:53,920
meaning it doesn't exist,
So there's no need to check.

564
00:43:54,520 --> 00:43:56,680
But the fact
that you want to see my tablet

565
00:43:58,880 --> 00:44:01,520
- tells me that...
- There's nothing to it.

566
00:44:02,120 --> 00:44:06,199
I wanted to see it
because I don't trust you.

567
00:44:06,200 --> 00:44:09,560
You might fake something to accuse me.

568
00:44:10,600 --> 00:44:12,120
But if you say there is none,

569
00:44:13,600 --> 00:44:15,120
I will believe you.

570
00:44:22,360 --> 00:44:25,080
About me being in your room...

571
00:44:26,040 --> 00:44:27,560
I won't tell anyone.

572
00:44:46,280 --> 00:44:47,920
Hey, where are you?

573
00:44:49,400 --> 00:44:50,799
Come home right now.

574
00:44:50,800 --> 00:44:53,160
I think Claire's acting strange.

575
00:45:06,280 --> 00:45:07,440
Mom.

576
00:45:08,080 --> 00:45:09,519
What's the hurry?

577
00:45:09,520 --> 00:45:12,560
I told you to hurry
because something happened.

578
00:45:14,640 --> 00:45:17,119
The thing about Claire acting strange.

579
00:45:17,120 --> 00:45:18,279
I agree.

580
00:45:18,280 --> 00:45:19,520
How?

581
00:45:20,200 --> 00:45:23,679
Out of nowhere today,
she lashed out at the executive board.

582
00:45:23,680 --> 00:45:24,880
Threatened to fire them.

583
00:45:26,040 --> 00:45:27,279
So what?

584
00:45:27,280 --> 00:45:29,200
That's just how she is.

585
00:45:29,840 --> 00:45:33,919
Yes. But since she came back,
she hadn't been the same, until today

586
00:45:33,920 --> 00:45:36,040
when she went back to her old self.

587
00:45:38,320 --> 00:45:39,720
How was she strange with you?

588
00:45:41,880 --> 00:45:45,160
I overheard her talking to Chan
about your dad.

589
00:45:45,960 --> 00:45:47,400
Are you sure...

590
00:45:48,000 --> 00:45:50,480
he won't suspect anything
about my shellfish allergy?

591
00:45:56,760 --> 00:45:58,600
Why would she say that?

592
00:46:00,000 --> 00:46:01,320
That's my question too.

593
00:46:03,240 --> 00:46:04,320
What does it sound like?

594
00:46:05,400 --> 00:46:09,080
It sounds like they're deceiving Dad.

595
00:46:10,040 --> 00:46:10,880
Yes.

596
00:46:12,920 --> 00:46:16,160
Then don't tell Dad about this yet.

597
00:46:17,480 --> 00:46:20,440
I thought you'd want me
to tell him immediately.

598
00:46:23,320 --> 00:46:27,200
But you know this might
change things for us, right?

599
00:46:27,960 --> 00:46:28,919
I do.

600
00:46:28,920 --> 00:46:32,440
But you know Chan and Claire
aren't that easy to deal with.

601
00:46:33,720 --> 00:46:34,919
Trust me.

602
00:46:34,920 --> 00:46:37,399
Don't tell Dad about this yet.

603
00:46:37,400 --> 00:46:39,160
Wait until we're sure first.

604
00:46:43,360 --> 00:46:47,480
Excuse me. The chairman wants you two
to join him at the dining table.

605
00:46:58,400 --> 00:47:00,159
I'm not hungry yet.

606
00:47:00,160 --> 00:47:01,560
Do I really have to eat?

607
00:47:03,440 --> 00:47:05,680
He said he wanted to talk to us.

608
00:47:07,400 --> 00:47:08,800
Do you know what it's about?

609
00:47:13,320 --> 00:47:14,600
You're already here?

610
00:47:16,480 --> 00:47:18,039
Did you wait long?

611
00:47:18,040 --> 00:47:19,240
No.

612
00:47:20,000 --> 00:47:22,000
Sit down. Let's eat together.

613
00:47:23,160 --> 00:47:24,360
Sit down.

614
00:47:30,560 --> 00:47:33,400
Have you recovered
from your shellfish allergy?

615
00:47:34,600 --> 00:47:36,520
Can you eat something heavy now?

616
00:47:37,880 --> 00:47:39,119
Pretty much.

617
00:47:39,120 --> 00:47:42,480
As long as there's no shellfish,
I can eat it.

618
00:47:43,160 --> 00:47:45,400
Did the doctor say what caused it?

619
00:47:46,360 --> 00:47:50,240
Because I remember before this,
you were a lobster lover.

620
00:47:57,080 --> 00:47:59,480
A person's cells change with age.

621
00:48:00,280 --> 00:48:02,240
The doctor says
the same thing, right, sir?

622
00:48:05,080 --> 00:48:07,120
Shall we change the subject?

623
00:48:07,640 --> 00:48:11,320
Talking about stressful things
will just ruin the food.

624
00:48:15,000 --> 00:48:15,840
Cha.

625
00:48:17,360 --> 00:48:20,080
Do you know that this part

626
00:48:20,720 --> 00:48:22,360
is the best part,

627
00:48:23,240 --> 00:48:26,040
and my favorite part to eat?

628
00:48:28,560 --> 00:48:29,800
But I'll let you have it.

629
00:48:31,200 --> 00:48:32,400
Give me your bowl.

630
00:48:43,360 --> 00:48:44,720
Enjoy it.

631
00:48:45,600 --> 00:48:46,560
- Eat.
- Cha.

632
00:48:47,600 --> 00:48:50,839
Dad gave you
his favorite part of the fish.

633
00:48:50,840 --> 00:48:52,520
Why haven't you thanked him?

634
00:48:54,160 --> 00:48:56,240
- Thank you, Dad.
- It's nothing.

635
00:48:58,040 --> 00:49:01,480
Do you know why I gave you the best part?

636
00:49:02,960 --> 00:49:03,880
Why?

637
00:49:05,880 --> 00:49:08,200
Because it's the only thing
you'll ever get from me!

638
00:49:13,840 --> 00:49:15,040
Honey.

639
00:49:15,600 --> 00:49:17,040
What is it?

640
00:49:17,640 --> 00:49:22,360
How dare you use your power to force
the executive board to remove Claire?

641
00:49:25,240 --> 00:49:28,760
Are you going to let someone
with amnesia run the company?

642
00:49:29,440 --> 00:49:31,880
If you weren't biased
because she's your blood,

643
00:49:32,960 --> 00:49:35,599
you would know
I did what I did for the company.

644
00:49:35,600 --> 00:49:37,520
I'm not here to listen to your excuses.

645
00:49:39,200 --> 00:49:42,000
I'm here to tell you to not do
anything like this again!

646
00:49:45,280 --> 00:49:46,760
Honey.

647
00:49:47,520 --> 00:49:50,400
I know that you love Claire very much.

648
00:49:52,520 --> 00:49:54,320
But if you found out she was...

649
00:49:55,280 --> 00:49:57,560
hiding something from you,

650
00:50:01,840 --> 00:50:03,360
what would you say?

651
00:50:07,240 --> 00:50:08,280
What is it, Claire?

652
00:50:09,360 --> 00:50:11,480
- Mom.
- Let me tell him.

653
00:50:12,080 --> 00:50:15,760
So your dad can wake up
and see things for what they are.

654
00:50:18,200 --> 00:50:21,959
I overheard Claire and Chan

655
00:50:21,960 --> 00:50:25,560
talk about
her shellfish allergy being a lie.

656
00:50:38,480 --> 00:50:39,840
What is this, Claire?

657
00:51:00,440 --> 00:51:03,839
I'm starting to wonder
if she's the real Claire or an impostor.

658
00:51:03,840 --> 00:51:06,399
Claire's memory hasn't fully returned.

659
00:51:06,400 --> 00:51:09,919
<i>But if you want to take over this duty,
I'm happy to step aside.</i>

660
00:51:09,920 --> 00:51:13,599
Some people might have a side
you've never seen.

661
00:51:13,600 --> 00:51:16,959
<i>Or they hide it
because they don't want you to see it.</i>

662
00:51:16,960 --> 00:51:17,959
What did you say?

663
00:51:17,960 --> 00:51:19,919
<i>Socialite Claire's in the news again?</i>

664
00:51:19,920 --> 00:51:22,359
<i>The only way to solve this problem is</i>

665
00:51:22,360 --> 00:51:27,160
you have to show everyone that
you're the same old Claire.

666
00:51:27,760 --> 00:51:29,680
I can do this.
